modules.description: Provides functions to compare public keys for equality and manages structured data representing SSH RSA certificates, including valid principals, validity timestamps, and extensions. Works with cryptographic types such as DSA, RSA, and Ed25519 public keys, along with certificate-specific records containing signing keys and signature data. Used to validate certificate authenticity, verify principal identities, and ensure time-bound access control in secure communication protocols.

Provides functions to load, parse, and manipulate SSH private keys and their associated certificates, including DSA, RSA, and Ed25519 key types. Works with raw byte blobs and structured key representations, enabling cryptographic operations like signing and verification. Used to generate and validate SSH certificate signatures in secure authentication workflows.

Parses SSH-agent requests and responses, handling both standard and extended message formats. Works with custom types representing SSH agent messages and raw byte streams. Used to process client-side agent requests and server-side agent responses in secure communication protocols.

Handles serialization of SSH agent requests and responses into HTTP messages using Faraday. Operates on custom types 'a ssh_agent_request and 'a ssh_agent_response. Used to encode protocol-specific data for network transmission in SSH agent communication.

Provides parsers and serializers for the ssh-agent protocol using angstrom and faraday, along with functions to construct and manage agent requests and responses. Works with binary data streams, private key structures (RSA, Ed25519), and agent message formats. Used to implement agent interactions such as adding keys to the agent, querying available identities, and handling authentication challenges.

Manages SSH agent communication by parsing, serializing, and validating cryptographic keys and certificates. Supports RSA, DSA, and Ed25519 key types, with operations for comparing public keys, verifying signatures, and checking certificate validity. Processes agent requests and responses, converting between custom message types and HTTP representations for network transmission. Enables secure authentication by ensuring key integrity, validating principals, and handling time-bound access controls.
